lead_paragraph: Maria Sharapova withstood a strong first set from the Greek qualifier Eleni Daniilidou before moving into the quarterfinals of the Linz Open in Austria with a 7-5, 6-1 victory. Sharapova will move above Justine Henin-Hardenne to take the No. 2 ranking if she reaches Sunday’s final.
